correctness.rationale: Multiple values are incorrect, untraceable, or violate schema intent. Key issues: (1) Material identity: materialDeposited is set to ZnO, but the article deposits Al-doped ZnO (AZO) with a Zn–Al–O interface via PEALD; aldMethod lists only ZnO and omits the Zn–Al–O subcycle. (2) Reactants: precursor list wrongly labels TMA under compound Al2O3; the article uses DEZ and TMA with O plasma to form Zn–Al–O, not Al2O3 cycles. coReactant list lacks an explicit entry for the Zn–Al–O subcycle. (3) Dosing/purge times: co-reactant dose is 15 s and purges are 10 s (after precursor) and 6 s (after plasma), but the JSON records 15 ms, 10 ms, and 6 ms; units must be MilliSEC with correct numeric values (15000, 10000, 6000). (4) Flow rates and units: 100 sccm applies to the O plasma (RPS), Ar carrier/purge is 50 sccm; precursorFlow=100 is not reported. Units are given as SCM-PER-MIN but numeric values are in sccm (off by 10^6). coReactantFlow and purgingGasFlow should be converted to 1.0e-4 and 5.0e-5 SCM-PER-MIN respectively. (5) Pressure: article states below 1 Torr; JSON fixes it at 1 mmHg without the inequality (minor but not exact). (6) Thickness control: growthPerCycle (0.26 Å) and filmThickness (130 nm) are not reported; only ‘500 total cycles’ is stated. saturation=True and nucleationPeriod=10 cycles are not supported by the text. (7) Plasma power 2500 W is correct; reactor name is correct, but manufacturer “Not Found” and deliveryMethod “Not Found” are not factual. (8) SupercycleDesign sequence 14:1 (ZnO:Zn–Al–O) matches one studied case; okay. (9) Material properties: many values are fabricated or not reported (refractiveIndex, absorptionCoefficient, bandGap value/method, uniformity, conformality aspect ratio, filmDensity). filmComposition.atomicRatio ‘14:1:1’ confuses supercycle ratio with elemental atomic ratio (not given). ElementalConcentration 85.5% is unlabeled and untraceable. Roughness ~4.5 nm at 200 °C is supported. Crystallinity polycrystalline (XRD/HRTEM) is supported. (10) Electrical properties: resistivity is wrong in magnitude and unit; 6.6×10^-3 Ω·cm at 200 °C corresponds to 6.6×10^-5 Ω·m, but JSON gives 0.0066 Ω·m. Carrier density and mobility values are not reported numerically; JSON values are untraceable. (11) DeviceProperties: TFT metrics (μ_FE, V_TH, SS, on/off) are not present in the article (device is electrochromic, not a TFT); these entries are fabricated. (12) Traceability: numerous fields are guessed or inconsistent with the paper. Correct by: updating material to AZO; fixing dosing/purge times and flow units/assignments; removing unreported properties (or leave optional fields blank); correcting resistivity to 6.6e-5 Ω·m; avoiding invented TFT device data; revising reactant compounds to reflect Zn–Al–O interface rather than Al2O3.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains multiple ungrounded or incorrect values, with several schema inconsistencies. Key issues: (1) Missing processes: the article reports multiple ALD conditions (supercycle M=9,14,19,24 and temperatures 100, 150, 200, 250 °C with 500 total cycles each), but only a single process (200 °C, 14:1) is represented. Separate process instances should be added for each distinct condition set. (2) Material mislabeling: aldSystem.materialDeposited is set to ZnO, but the deposited film is Al-doped ZnO with a Zn–Al–O interface (AZO). (3) Reactants/co-reactant: coReactant is only listed for ZnO; the O plasma co-reactant also applies to the DEZ/TMA subcycle (Zn–Al–O), and this is not represented. (4) Dosing/purge times are wrong by three orders of magnitude and units are inconsistent: article gives 15 s (co-reactant), 10 s (purge after precursor), 6 s (purge after co-reactant); extraction uses 15 ms, 10 ms, 6 ms instead of 15000, 10000, 6000 ms per schema. (5) Flow rates: 100 sccm is reported for the O source (RPS); assigning 100 sccm to precursorFlow is unsupported. Purging Ar flow 50 sccm is correct. (6) Pressure: article states “below 1 Torr”; extraction fixes it at 1 Torr equivalent. (7) Thickness control: growth-per-cycle (0.26 Å) and film thickness (130 nm) are not provided in the article (thickness is in Table S1, not present); these values are untraceable. (8) Saturation=True and nucleationPeriod=10 cycles are not supported by the text. (9) Supercycle design: counts 14:1 match one case, but other reported M values (9,19,24) are missing as separate processes. (10) Electrical units: resistivity is given as 0.0066 Ω·m; the article reports 6.6×10^-3 Ω·cm at 200 °C, which equals 6.6×10^-5 Ω·m. The current extraction is off by 100×. Carrier density and mobility numeric values are not reported in the text; provided numbers are ungrounded. (11) Optical properties: refractive index, absorption coefficient, and numeric band gap are not reported; insertion of 1.9, 0.01, and 3.3 eV is untraceable. Transmittance (91% at 200 °C) reported in the article is not properly captured. (12) Composition: ‘atomicRatio’ as 14:1:1 confuses cycle ratio with elemental ratio; elemental concentrations (85.5%) are unreported. (13) Device properties: TFT metrics (μFE, VTH, SS, ION/IOFF) and device structure are not part of this article (which reports electrochromic device performance), so these values are inappropriate and untraceable. (14) Placeholder values like “Not Found” for reactor manufacturer and deliveryMethod and invented values for uniformity, conformality, film density violate the traceability/completeness requirements. Properties to add/review: add separate processes for each M and temperature; correct dosing/purge times and units; correct resistivity unit conversion; provide only reported/traceable values (RPS power 2500 W, O2 flow 100 sccm, Ar 50 sccm, 500 cycles, temperatures, PET substrate, transmittance 91%, roughness 4.515 nm at 200 °C); replace materialDeposited with AZO/Zn–Al–O; include the supercycle design for each M; remove or leave unspecified values not supported by the article (GPC, film thickness unless Table S1 is available, refractive index, band gap, TFT metrics, atomic ratios, uniformity/conformality/film density) or supply them if traceable. Overall, many fields are incorrect, untraceable, or missing, so completeness is very poor.
